  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who has shown remorse by partially restituting the stolen funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty, a 10-year sentence requested by the spectator is grossly disproportionate to the amount stolen and the defendant's background. Considering the nature of the white-collar crime and the absence of a criminal record, a sentence of 6 months serves as a punitive measure that balances justice with the potential for rehabilitation.",
  "verdict": 6
}
